**STRICT TIER ENFORCEMENT WITH SPECIFIC FEATURES**:

1. **Internal Tier** (Sybertnetics only)
   - **Autonomous Operation**: Full self-directed coding without human input
   - **Self-Modification**: Can rewrite own codebase in Runa
   - **Learning**: All code is used for training to improve SyberSuite
   - **Privacy**: No privacy - all internal work improves our systems
   - **LLM Access**: All 5 LLMs simultaneously with unlimited tokens
   - **Token Limit**: UNLIMITED
   - **Code Generation**: Entire applications from single prompts
   - **Multi-Agent**: Full coordination with SyberSuite agents
   - **Debugging**: Predictive debugging, auto-fixes without asking
   - **Performance**: No throttling, maximum speed
   - **AI Development**: ONLY tier allowed to develop AI/ML/LLM systems

2. **Enterprise Tier** ($2000+/month)
   - **Privacy**: DEFAULT zero retention, but orgs can opt-in to training
   - **Privacy Control**: Organization-wide privacy settings in admin panel
   - **LLM Access**: 4 LLMs (all except shared reasoning), private instances
   - **Token Limit**: 10M tokens/month (customizable in contract)
   - **Code Generation**: Full modules and complex systems (except AI/ML)
   - **Learning**: If opted-in, learning stays within organization
   - **Deployment**: On-premise option available
   - **Support**: 24/7 dedicated support, custom feature requests
   - **Customization**: Custom model fine-tuning on company codebase (if opted-in)
   - **Collaboration**: Team features, shared knowledge graphs
   - **Compliance**: SOC2, HIPAA, GDPR compliance features
   - **API Access**: Full API for custom integrations
   - **AI Development**: PROHIBITED - Cannot develop AI/ML/LLM systems

3. **Professional Tier** ($200/month)
   - **Privacy**: DEFAULT retention for training, can opt-out in settings
   - **Privacy Control**: Individual toggle in settings menu (persists across sessions)
   - **LLM Access**: 3 LLMs (coding, architecture, documentation)
   - **Token Limit**: 2M tokens/month
   - **Code Generation**: 
     - Complete features and modules
     - Complex refactoring
     - Multi-file operations
     - Small applications (up to ~5000 lines)
   - **Learning**: Personal learning, improves over time (if opted-in)
   - **Debugging**: Interactive debugging with suggestions
   - **Refactoring**: AI-assisted refactoring
   - **Testing**: Test generation and coverage analysis
   - **Documentation**: Auto-documentation generation
   - **Languages**: All language support via Runa translation
   - **Performance**: Standard priority, <100ms responses

4. **Hobby Tier** ($20/month)
   - **Privacy**: MANDATORY data retention for LLM training
   - **Privacy Control**: None - agreement to training is part of tier
   - **LLM Access**: 1 LLM (coding specialist only)
   - **Token Limit**: 500K tokens/month
   - **Code Generation**: 
     - Functions and classes
     - Small features (up to ~500 lines)
     - Basic refactoring
     - Cannot generate entire applications
   - **Completion**: Context-aware code completion
   - **Syntax**: Syntax checking and error detection
   - **Languages**: Top 20 popular languages
   - **Learning**: Basic pattern recognition + contributes to global model
   - **Documentation**: Read-only access to generated docs
   - **Support**: Community support only
   - **Performance**: Best-effort, <500ms responses

**Privacy Implementation**:
```python
# Enterprise: Default OFF, can turn ON
if user.tier == Tier.ENTERPRISE:
    data_retention = org_settings.get('enable_training', False)

# Professional: Default ON, can turn OFF  
if user.tier == Tier.PROFESSIONAL:
    data_retention = user_settings.get('enable_training', True)

# Hobby: Always ON
if user.tier == Tier.HOBBY:
    data_retention = True  # No option to disable

# Internal: Configurable
if user.tier == Tier.INTERNAL:
    data_retention = user_settings.get('enable_training', True)
```


Always check tier permissions before implementing features.